Class and Objects:
- What is a class: A class is a Template
- What is an Object: Copies of the class

-Select the Sheet/image/folder you want to copy by clicking on it
-Do right click and select the Copy option
-IDENTIFY THE PLACE WHERE YOU WANT TO CREATE THE COPY
-Right click on the place and Select Paste option
-Now again select the pasted Sheet/image/folder and do right click
-Select the rename option and change the name of Sheet/image/folder as per your needs

Syntax:
NameOfTheClassWhoseObjectYouWantToCreate nameYouWantToGiveToYourObject = new NameOfTheClassWhoseObjectYouWantToCreate();

Class ---> Company
Company apple = new Company();
Company microsoft = new Company();

Class ---> Abacus
Abacus slate = new Abacus();

Class ---> LivingBeings
LivingBeings human = new LivingBeings();
LivingBeings plants = new LivingBeings();
LivingBeings animals =new LivingBeings();

===========================MEMORY MANAGEMENT==========================================
-Memory is divided into 2 sections
  -HEAP  : Stores the object
  -STACK : Stores the reference variables of the objects







